Use feynman technique + AI to learn

The four steps mirror the actual Feynman method:

Pick a topic — specific beats vague. "How does RAM work" is better than "computers".
Explain it simply — the act of writing it out in plain language reveals what you actually know vs. what you just recognise.
Find your gaps — the moments you went blank or had to guess are gold. They tell you exactly where to go back in your notes or source material.
Review & repeat — hit "Ask Claude to fill my gaps" and it'll explain those specific parts to you, which you can then try to re-explain again.

The iPad is a great tool for this — apps like Notability or GoodNotes let you handwrite, which also tends to help retention more than typing.

